description:
Joe Raedle / Getty Images
Louisiana Gov. Bobby Jindal announced on Tuesday evening that he is dropping out of the GOP race for president."This is not my time. I've come to the realization that this is not my time. So I came here to announce that I'm suspending my campaign for president of the United States," Jindal said on Fox News' Special Report with Bret Baier.This is a developing story. Check back for updates and follow BuzzFeed News on Twitter.
title: Bobby Jindal Drops Out Of The GOP Presidential Race
